What do you mean? You will get a compiler error in any case where there is a break or continue in an outermost while block. There's nothing odd or uncommon about that. Here's something closer to a real program:<p><pre><code>    int main(void)
    {
        while (1) {
            char c = getchar();
            if (c == 'q') break;
            process(c);
        }
        return 0;
    }</code></pre>
